# Discord Chat Analysis for ðŸ’¬-coders

## 1. Summary:
The chat primarily revolves around ElizaOS agent deployment issues. A user named Rabbidfly encountered context size limitations with their Telegram chat history database (1GB), receiving 400 errors from OpenAI. The issue was resolved by removing a duplicate character.ts file that was loading alongside their custom agent. Other discussions included questions about ElizaOS being Bun-only, hosting options for agents with large databases, and Telegram plugin issues in cloud deployments. Users also reported and moderators handled a scammer in the channel. There was a brief mention of a Chinese "agent" with MCP knowledge base functionality, though details were limited. The conversation demonstrates the community's collaborative troubleshooting approach for ElizaOS implementation challenges.

## 2. FAQ:
Q: Is elizaos now bun only? (asked by Mr. Kiter) A: Unanswered
Q: Which version is the most production ready? (asked by z1) A: Unanswered
Q: Can I code recency truncation logic in my custom action? (asked by Rabbidfly) A: Unanswered
Q: Could we connect this Chinese agent with MCP knowledge base to Eliza cloud? (asked by DearDaniel) A: Unanswered
Q: Is there a decent hosting alternative to Railway that allows FTP access for a 1GB database? (asked by Rabbidfly) A: Hetzner or OVH VPSes, WholesaleInternet and BuyVM are also good (answered by Odilitime)

## 3. Help Interactions:
Helper: sayonara | Helpee: Rabbidfly | Context: Needed hosting solution for agent with 1GB database after Railway didn't allow FTP uploads | Resolution: Suggested using Postgres with dump upload or creating custom image with pglite data for Railway
Helper: 0xbbjoker | Helpee: Rabbidfly | Context: Context size too large error with OpenAI due to 1GB chat history database | Resolution: Helped troubleshoot by asking about setup and how chat history was being added to context
Helper: sayonara | Helpee: Rabbidfly | Context: Telegram plugin issues in DigitalOcean deployment | Resolution: Offered to check and fix the issue the next day
